<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230570" authority="Santschi, 1930" authorityName="Santschi" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Aethiopopone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Aethiopopone rufiventris var. chariensis" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Aethiopopone rufiventris var. chariensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="rufiventris" variety="chariensis">Aethiopopone rufiventris Sants. v. chariensis</taxonomicName>
Sants.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="50">
(= 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:144439" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Sphinctomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphinctomyrmex chariensis Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Sphinctomyrmex chariensis Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="rufiventris" variety="chariensis">Sphinctomyrmex rufiventris v. chariensis</taxonomicName>
Santschi, 1915, ibid., p. 245).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="50">
Soudan francais, Senenkou, 250 km. en aval de Koulouba (AnDRIEU). 3 [[ male ]] captures a la lumiere. Decembre 1928. En 1915, quand je decrivis cette espece en la rapportant au genre 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2433" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Sphinctomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphinctomyrmex Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Sphinctomyrmex Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphinctomyrmex</taxonomicName>
,. l'habitat de celui-ci etait considere comme etant le Bresil, l'Australie et l'Inde, et le [[ male ]] etait encore inconnu. Or, le [[ male ]] de 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:36423" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Sphinctomyrmex" genus.bestMatchDistance="91" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphinctomyrmex rufiventris Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Sphinctomyrmex rufiventris Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufiventris">S. rufiventris</taxonomicName>
, avec ses caracteres de 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230571" genus="Prodorylinas" lsidName="Uploaded - Prodorylinas" lsidName-HNS="Uploaded - Prodorylinas" pageNumber="50" rank="genus">Prodorylinas</taxonomicName>
, surtout ses segments
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="51" pageNumber="50">
abdominaux etrangles, son habitat intermediaire, me fit risquer une identification pareille a celle que firent Forel et Emery en rapportant a ce genre les 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:146952" authority="Emery, 1893" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eusphinctus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eusphinctus Emery" lsidName-HNS="Eusphinctus Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eusphinctus</taxonomicName>
du vieux monde. Ce n'est du reste qu'en 1918 que Wheeler fit la distinction generique, ne considerant plus que comme 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2433" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Sphinctomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphinctomyrmex Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Sphinctomyrmex Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphinctomyrmex</taxonomicName>
la [[ queen ]] S. Stali Mayr, du Bresil. En elevant au rang de genre le sous-genre 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:146952" authority="Emery, 1893" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eusphinctus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eusphinctus Emery" lsidName-HNS="Eusphinctus Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eusphinctus</taxonomicName>
Em. pour les especes indo-australiennes, il le divise en trois sous-genres: 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:146952" authority="Emery, 1893" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eusphinctus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eusphinctus Emery" lsidName-HNS="Eusphinctus Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eusphinctus</taxonomicName>
, Notosphinc-tus et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:147293" authority="Wheeler W.M., 1918" authorityName="Wheeler W.M." authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Zasphinctus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zasphinctus Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Zasphinctus Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Zasphinctus</taxonomicName>
. Cela etant donne, je me vois oblige de creer un
nouveau genre pour l'espece africaine. Les caracteres de celle-ci tiennent des G. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2433" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Sphinctomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphinctomyrmex Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Sphinctomyrmex Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphinctomyrmex</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2431" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cerapachys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerapachys Smith" lsidName-HNS="Cerapachys Smith" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cerapachys</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2432" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Simopone Forel" lsidName-HNS="Simopone Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Simopone</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
